# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge
We pledge to make participation in this project a welcoming, respectful, and harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of background, identity, or experience. We expect contributors to treat each other with courtesy and consideration.

## Our Standards
Examples of positive behavior:
- Use welcoming and inclusive language.
- Be respectful and considerate in communication.
- Give constructive feedback and assume good intent.
- Respect privacy and personal boundaries.

Examples of unacceptable behavior:
- Harassment, intimidation, or discrimination of any kind.
- Insults, derogatory comments, or personal attacks.
- Public or private harassment, stalking, or sustained disruption.
- Posting sexually explicit or violent content.

## Enforcement Responsibilities
Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying and enforcing this Code of Conduct. Maintainers have the authority to remove, edit, or reject contributions, and to restrict or ban contributors for behavior that violates this Code of Conduct.

## Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces and activities, including:
- Repository issues and pull requests
- Project discussion forums and mailing lists
- Chat channels and social media accounts run by the project
- In-person and virtual events organized by the project

## Enforcement
If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to the project maintainers at **maintainers@example.com**. Reports should include:
- A description of the incident
- Names or handles of the people involved
- Links, screenshots, or other supporting evidence

All reports will be handled promptly and confidentially to the extent possible.

## Enforcement Guidelines
When a report is received, maintainers will:
1. Acknowledge receipt of the report within a reasonable timeframe.  
2. Investigate the report confidentially and objectively.  
3. Take appropriate and proportional actions, which may include:
   - Private warning to the offender
   - Request for public or private apology
   - Temporary suspension of contribution privileges
   - Permanent ban from project spaces
4. Document actions taken and, when appropriate, inform the community of outcomes without revealing private details.

## Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org. The Contributor Covenant is distributed under the Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal license.

## Contact and Revision
- **Contact:** maintainer email **maintainers@example.com** (replace with real address).  
- **Revision:** This Code of Conduct may be updated by project maintainers. Changes will be documented in the project history.
